    public class OperandPusher
extends java.lang.Object

    Pushes non-operator items (operands) onto the stack.

    This is currently the only command that pushes anything onto the operands stack in execute

      • execute

        public void execute(Stack<java.lang.String> operands,
                    java.lang.String token)
        Execute the arithmetic command using the provided operator and operands.

        This executor pushes the operand stored in the parameter token onto the stack. i.e. if it looks like a number, then push it onto the operands stack.

        Specified by:
        execute in interface Operator
        Parameters:
        operands - the subjects of the arithmetic operation
        token - Either an operand or operator applied to the operands
